Patti Smith will be marking the 40th anniversary of her seminal debut album Horses by launching a world tour. It’s still a bit early for exact details, since it’s not going down for another year, but Smith recently let Rolling Stone in what she was planning. According… Patti Smith to Celebrate 40th Anniversary of ‘Horses’ with a World Tour October 14, 2014 News Easter, which included her breakthrough hit 'Because the Night,' co-written with Bruce Springsteen. Born in 1946 in Chicago, Patti Smith has earned a reputation as the 'Godmother of Punk,' but her performing talent transcends rock. It is an amalgam of penetrating words combined with music, and laced with a manic on-stage style that delivers the impact of her lyrics with a punctuating insistence.
